</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6e5ab2664b422d53eb0c7df3b87e1360d75ad9af" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.09ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \theta }"></span>, the <i><a href="/wiki/External_angle" class="mw-redirect" title="External angle">external angle</a></i> at the same vertex is defined to be its <a href="/wiki/Supplementary_angle" class="mw-redirect" title="Supplementary angle">supplement</a> <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \pi -\theta }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
